## Summary

# Session Summary

## Objective
Implement and document a new `--summary-skill` workflow in `git-memento` so commit/amend notes can store a reviewed markdown summary while preserving full session data in a separate audit notes ref.

## Implemented Changes
- Added `--summary-skill <skill|default>` to:
  - `git memento commit <session-id> ...`
  - `git memento amend <session-id> ...`
- Added summary mode behavior:
  - Generate markdown summary via provider command.
  - Print summary and require user confirmation.
  - If rejected, require a custom retry prompt and regenerate.
- Added dual-note storage model:
  - Summary note in `refs/notes/commits`.
  - Full session note in `refs/notes/memento-full-audit`.
- Added provider summary config:
  - `memento.<provider>.summary.bin`
  - `memento.<provider>.summary.args`
- Added default summary command templates:
  - Codex: `exec {prompt}`
  - Claude: `-p {prompt}`
- Added default skill mapping to in-repo summary skill.
- Updated notes sync/carry flows to include both refs.
- Updated docs and skill files (repo + local skill copy) for summary support.

## Files Touched (high-level)
- CLI/domain/config/provider/workflows/docs were updated, including:
  - `src/GitMemento.Cli/CliArgs.fs`
